{"info": {"author": "Adam Johnson", "author_email": "me@adamj.eu", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Framework :: Pytest", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Natural Language :: English", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only"], "description": "==============\npytest-reverse\n==============\n\n.. image:: https://github.com/adamchainz/pytest-reverse/workflows/CI/badge.svg?branch=master\n   :target: https://github.com/adamchainz/pytest-reverse/actions?workflow=CI\n\n.. image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pytest-reverse.svg\n   :target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-reverse\n\n.. image:: https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg\n   :target: https://github.com/python/black\n\nPytest plugin to reverse test order.\n\n-----\nUsage\n-----\n\nInstall from pip with:\n\n.. code-block:: bash\n\n    python -m pip install pytest-reverse\n\nPython 3.5 to 3.8 supported.\n\nPytest will automatically find the plugin and use it when you run ``pytest``.\nYou can reverse test order by passing the ``--reverse`` flag:\n\n.. code-block:: bash\n\n    pytest --reverse\n\nYou can make this always apply by adding it to the ``addopts`` setting in your\n``pytest.ini`` (or `other configuration\nfile <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/customize.html#adding-default-options>`__):\n\n.. code-block:: ini\n\n    [pytest]\n    addopts = --reverse\n\n-------\nHistory\n-------\n\nI'm the creator and maintainer of\n`pytest-randomly <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-randomly>`__, a plugin\nfor randomly ordering tests. @thbde opened an issue there pointing to the paper\n`Empirically revisiting the test independence\nassumption <https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/2610384.2610404>`__, which covers\ntest reordering techniques. It turns out that reversal is nearly as effective\nas randomization.\n\nTest reversal is available `in Django's test\nrunner <https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/django-admin/#cmdoption-test-reverse>`__.\nI figured such an option or plugin would exist for pytest already, but it\ndidn't, so I made it here.\n\n-------\nHistory\n-------\n\n1.0.1 (2020-04-08)\n------------------\n\n* Run first to avoid interfering with ``--failed-first`` flag\n  (`docs <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/cache.html>`__).\n\n1.0.0 (2020-04-03)\n------------------\n\n* First release on PyPI.\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/x-rst", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/adamchainz/pytest-reverse", "keywords": "pytest,reverse", "license": "BSD", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "pytest-reverse", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pytest-reverse/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pytest-reverse/", "project_urls": {"Changelog": "https://github.com/adamchainz/pytest-reverse/blob/master/HISTORY.rst", "Homepage": "https://github.com/adamchainz/pytest-reverse"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pytest-reverse/1.0.1/", "requires_dist": ["pytest"], "requires_python": ">=3.5", "summary": "Pytest plugin to reverse test order.", "version": "1.0.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <a href=\"https://github.com/adamchainz/pytest-reverse/actions?workflow=CI\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"https://github.com/adamchainz/pytest-reverse/workflows/CI/badge.svg?branch=master\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/7982cd88d764db314e9c04cdcd97bf9b7b8de236/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f6164616d636861696e7a2f7079746573742d726576657273652f776f726b666c6f77732f43492f62616467652e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pytest-reverse\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pytest-reverse.svg\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/c5225885706d941126c5f60c63ef61fd5c1326ec/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f707970692f762f7079746573742d726576657273652e737667\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/python/black\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/fbfdc7754183ecf079bc71ddeabaf88f6cbc5c00/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f636f64652532307374796c652d626c61636b2d3030303030302e737667\"></a>\n<p>Pytest plugin to reverse test order.</p>\n<div id=\"usage\">\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>Install from pip with:</p>\n<pre>python -m pip install pytest-reverse\n</pre>\n<p>Python 3.5 to 3.8 supported.</p>\n<p>Pytest will automatically find the plugin and use it when you run <tt>pytest</tt>.\nYou can reverse test order by passing the <tt><span class=\"pre\">--reverse</span></tt> flag:</p>\n<pre>pytest --reverse\n</pre>\n<p>You can make this always apply by adding it to the <tt>addopts</tt> setting in your\n<tt>pytest.ini</tt> (or <a href=\"https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/customize.html#adding-default-options\" rel=\"nofollow\">other configuration\nfile</a>):</p>\n<pre><span class=\"k\">[pytest]</span>\n<span class=\"na\">addopts</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s\">--reverse</span>\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div id=\"history\">\n<h2>History</h2>\n<p>I\u2019m the creator and maintainer of\n<a href=\"https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-randomly\" rel=\"nofollow\">pytest-randomly</a>, a plugin\nfor randomly ordering tests. @thbde opened an issue there pointing to the paper\n<a href=\"https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/2610384.2610404\" rel=\"nofollow\">Empirically revisiting the test independence\nassumption</a>, which covers\ntest reordering techniques. It turns out that reversal is nearly as effective\nas randomization.</p>\n<p>Test reversal is available <a href=\"https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/django-admin/#cmdoption-test-reverse\" rel=\"nofollow\">in Django\u2019s test\nrunner</a>.\nI figured such an option or plugin would exist for pytest already, but it\ndidn\u2019t, so I made it here.</p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"id1\">\n<h2>History</h2>\n<div id=\"id2\">\n<h3>1.0.1 (2020-04-08)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Run first to avoid interfering with <tt><span class=\"pre\">--failed-first</span></tt> flag\n(<a href=\"https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/cache.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">docs</a>).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"id3\">\n<h3>1.0.0 (2020-04-03)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>First release on PyPI.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6980021, "releases": {"1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "0036610c3ac82190c479f89e8a3c59c2", "sha256": "6e88b461bb3f419c01a0fc6cea3fdd8dd8b86e6978e640c2116e7462a367e482"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pytest_reverse-1.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": true, "md5_digest": "0036610c3ac82190c479f89e8a3c59c2", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 3736, "upload_time": "2020-04-03T19:06:15", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-03T19:06:15.124492Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/af/c3/7ff55aa3a7c98da0246d58af58e109f44bea2792471ff1128f375e910e7e/pytest_reverse-1.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "293c65bacd77b0aaaff92b276727ad6a", "sha256": "10bbd495b2144040fbf37e58e3537e8c6a4bad4e1d03a317eec010c36c5fd1c8"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pytest-reverse-1.0.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": true, "md5_digest": "293c65bacd77b0aaaff92b276727ad6a", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 5320, "upload_time": "2020-04-03T19:06:17", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-03T19:06:17.900028Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/87/e7/a949f686f94b10a38a23853abb6ee197a